The majority of these examples are written in Java and compiled with Maven:

    http://maven.apache.org/download.cgi

To build and run the Hadoop examples (WordCount, WordCountXML and WikiContributorsBatch), change into the directory of the project and:

    mvn package
    hadoop jar target/<projectname>-1.0-jar-with-dependencies.jar input output

To see how to run on a Hadoop cluster, see the Lambda Architecture chapter.

To build and run the Storm example (WikiContributorsSpeed), change into the directory of the project and:

    mvn compile
    mvn exec:java

There are a couple of utility projects written in Clojure (ExtractWikiContributors, ExtractWikiText). To compile and run these, change into the directory of the project and:

    lein run
